Ryan Dunn of Paramount’s ‘Jackass’ Stunt Movies Dies in Fiery Car Crash

-- B y   A n d y   F i x m e r
-- 
2011-06-21T00:19:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/ryan-dunn-of-paramount-s-jackass-stunt-movies-dies-in-fiery-car-crash.html
Ryan Dunn , a star of  Paramount
Pictures ’ “Jackass” movies and the MTV television show, died
in a car crash about 24 miles west of Philadelphia.  Dunn, 34, and an unidentified passenger died from injuries
sustained when his 2007 Porsche 911 GT3 left a roadway and burst
into flames,  police  in West Goshen Township,  Pennsylvania , said
today in a statement. Speed may have been a factor, police said.  The car was “fully engulfed in flames” when police
arrived at the scene at 2:38 a.m. local time, according to the
statement. Police said they are still trying to identify Dunn’s
passenger.  “We are devastated by this loss,” Dunn’s family said in a
statement issued by the entertainer’s talent agency William
Morris Endeavor. “We appreciate the support of Ryan’s fans
during this time, and we are grateful for your thoughts and
prayers. Ryan will be greatly missed, but he will forever remain
in our hearts.”  Dunn was a member of Johnny Knoxville’s band of amateur
stuntmen, appearing in the MTV show “Jackass” from 2000 to
2002, according to Amazon.com Inc.’s Imdb.com. He also starred
in Paramount’s “Jackass” film series that collected $248
million in worldwide ticket sales, according to Imbd.com.  Viacom
Inc. (VIA/B)  owns both MTV and Paramount.  To contact the reporter on this story:
